  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "Toss broccoli with olive oil, garlic, salt, pepper, and dill on a baking sheet.",
    "Roast for 15 minutes, or until tender and slightly browned.",
    "Remove from oven and deglaze with apple cider vinegar and lemon juice.",
    "Return to oven for an additional 2-3 minutes, or until slightly caramelized.",
    "Meanwhile, mix chopped parsley with a pinch of salt and pepper.",
    "Serve broccoli kebabs hot, topped with parsley mixture and a squeeze of lemon juice.",
    "Let cool slightly before serving, if desired.",
    "Garnish with additional parsley, if needed.",
    "Serve immediately, and enjoy!"
